				<h1 itemprop="headline" class="entry-title">Today in Small Business: Pizza for Everyone!</h1>
		<div class="story-meta-footer">
			<address class="byline author vcard" itemprop="author creator" itemtype="//schema.org/Person">
				By Gene Marks			</address>
			<!-- date published --><time class="dateline " datetime="2014-07-10T16:28:21+00:00" itemprop="datePublished">July 10, 2014 12:28 pm</time>
			<!-- date updated --><span class="visually-hidden updated">July 10, 2014 12:28 pm</span><button class="button comments-button  theme-kicker" data-skip-to-para-id="">
</button>
		</div>
			</header>
		<div class="entry-content"><div id="sharetools-story" class="sharetools theme-classic sharetools-story" data-shares="email|Email,facebook|Share,twitter|Tweet,save|Save,show-all|More,ad" data-url="//boss.blogs.nytimes.com/2014/07/10/today-in-small-business-pizza-for-everyone/" data-title="Today in Small Business: Pizza for Everyone!" data-description="Gasoline prices are falling. Employers say they are struggling to find qualified workers. And where are all of the start-ups?">
				<div class="ad sharetools-inline-article-ad"></div>
				<div id="MiddleLeft" class="ad middle-left-ad nocontent robots-nocontent"></div>
				</div><div class="inlineModule"><div class="entry"><h6 class="kicker"><a href="//boss.blogs.nytimes.com/category/dashboard/">Dashboard</a></h6><p class="summary">A daily roundup of small-business developments.</p></div></div>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Whatâs affecting me, my clients and other small-business owners today.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>The Economy</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Gasoline and crude oil <a href="//247wallst.com/energy-economy/2014/07/09/gasoline-and-crude-oil-prices-falling-as-refiners-increase-output/?">prices are falling</a> as refiners increase their output.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Jobless claims <a href="//online.wsj.com/articles/u-s-jobless-claims-fell-last-week-1404995546?mod=asia_home">continue to fall</a>.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Confident in the economy, the Federal Reserve offers details on <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/07/10/business/federal-reserve-june-minutes-detail-end-of-bond-buying-program-.html">the end of its bond-buying</a>.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ As of September, all European Union countries will be required to take fuller accounting of <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/07/10/business/international/eu-nations-counting-sex-and-drug-trades-toward-gdp.html">trade in sex, drugs and other underground businesses</a>.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Customer Service</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ A quick-thinking pilot <a href="//mashable.com/2014/07/09/pilot-pizza-delayed-flight/?">buys pizza</a> for everyone on a stranded flight.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Uber says it will <a href="//techcrunch.com/2014/07/08/uber-caps-surge-pricing-during-emergencies/">cap its pricing</a> during emergencies nationwide.  <span id="more-87117"></span></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Employees</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Most employers surveyed are <a href="//www.marketwired.com/press-release/employers-having-a-hard-time-finding-qualified-workers-1928248.htm">struggling to find</a> qualified workers.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Management</strong></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ TaskRabbit is <a href="//www.businessweek.com/articles/2014-07-10/taskrabbit-adds-insurance-to-make-trusting-strangers-easier#r=rss">offering insurance</a> to both the people who post tasks and those who perform them.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Health Care</strong></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Once derided as âDoc in a Boxâ medicine, <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/07/10/business/race-is-on-to-profit-from-rise-of-urgent-care.html">urgent care has mushroomed</a> into an estimated $14.5 billion business.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Social Media</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ A 17-year-old uses the World Cup (and social media) to <a href="//www.businessinsider.com/axelle-despiegelaere-gets-modeling-contract-after-viral-world-cup-photo-2014-7">land a modeling deal</a> with LâOreal.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Google uses <a href="//www.theverge.com/2014/7/9/5885169/google-crafts-world-cup-tweets-using-search-trends">search trends</a> to craft viral tweets.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Online</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ A guest blogger for the Daily Mail experiences <a href="//www.newstatesman.com/media/2014/07/your-family-are-losers-and-your-children-are-adopted-what-it-s-write-mailonlin">just how hateful</a> the Internet can be, and a sleeping baseball <a href="https://uk.eurosport.yahoo.com/blogs/world-of-sport/fan-fell-asleep-during-match-suing-millions-111548904.html?">fan&#8217;s lawsuit</a> tries to turn the tables on commenters.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ There are only a few ways to scale user growth, and <a href="//andrewchen.co/2014/07/08/theres-only-a-few-ways-to-scale-user-growth-and-heres-the-list/">hereâs the list.</a></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Marketing</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ How brands are using <a href="//www.fastcompany.com/3032732/most-creative-people/how-brands-are-using-your-best-instagram-shots-for-more-authentic-marketing">Instagram shots</a> for more authentic marketing.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Around the Country</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Sales of <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/07/09/us/washington-to-begin-sales-of-recreational-marijuana.html?_r=0">recreational marijuana</a> begin in Washington State.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Some customers are complaining that a bar in Minneapolis has a racist <a href="//pjmedia.com/tatler/2014/07/08/can-a-dress-code-be-racist/">dress code</a>.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ New York City will be <a href="//online.wsj.com/articles/new-york-city-mitigates-rules-fines-for-businesses-1404869910">reducing certain fines</a> on small businesses by more than a third.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Los Angeles hotel workers could get the <a href="//money.cnn.com/2014/07/09/news/economy/la-hotel-minimum-wage/index.html">highest minimum wage</a> in the United States.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Around the World</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Some Russian lawmakers are <a href="//www.thewire.com/business/2014/07/russian-lawmakers-complain-about-pornographic-money/374087/">complaining about</a> the countryâs &#8220;pornographic money.&#8221;</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Retail</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Walmart <a href="//www.mbtmag.com/news/2014/07/walmart%E2%80%99s-first-ever-made-usa-open-call-underway">opens its headquarters</a> so more than 500 manufacturers can pitch their products.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Some American-themed products are <a href="//www.news9.com/story/25970856/some-american-themed-products-are-actually-not-made-in-america">not made</a> in America.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Because of a recent hacking case, some experts warn customers to <a href="//www.bloombergview.com/articles/2014-07-09/don-t-buy-pizza-with-a-credit-card">beware of</a> using credit cards in small businesses.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Start-Up</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ James Pethokoukis asks where all of the start-ups are and questions the theory that <a href="//www.aei-ideas.org/2014/07/where-are-all-the-startups/">rising home values</a> should result in more new business creation and more jobs.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Some start-ups are offering ways to <a href="//dealbook.nytimes.com/2014/07/09/start-ups-make-political-organizing-mobile-ready/?_php=true&amp;_type=blogs&amp;_r=0">help people engage politically</a>.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Ideas</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ LG introduces wristbands that <a href="//www.entrepreneur.com/article/235480">let you track</a> your children.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ iBeacons are projected to break <a href="//www.mobilemarketingwatch.com/ibeacons-to-break-big-records-within-5-years-43096/?">records</a>.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ A chief executive <a href="//www.fastcompany.com/3032756/most-creative-people/the-electric-autonomous-future-of-mercedes-benz">takes a look</a> at the electric, autonomous future of Mercedes-Benz.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Technology</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Microsoft announces a <a href="//www.informationweek.com/cloud/software-as-a-service/microsoft-enhances-azure-office-365/d/d-id/1297162">raft of enhancements</a> to its cloud portfolio.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Quarterly shipments of tablet PCs are projected to <a href="//www.zdnet.com/quarterly-tablet-pc-shipments-to-fall-for-the-first-time-ever-7000031400/">fall for the first time</a>.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ With <a href="//blogs.wsj.com/digits/2014/07/09/with-google-offer-cloud-storage-gets-closer-to-free/">a new offer from Google</a>, cloud storage gets closer to free.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><em>Gene Marks owns the <a href="//www.marksgroup.net">Marks Group</a>, a Bala Cynwyd, Pa., consulting firm that helps clients with customer relationship management. You can follow him on <a href="https://www.twitter.com/genemarks">Twitter</a>.</em></p>
